Designed and built by world-renowned architects Rosario Candela and Gaetano Ajello in 1911, elegance itself has found its home here at 575 West End Avenue. Ranked among the most prestigious rental buildings in all of Manhattan, 575 offers world unparalleled service that has stood the test of time. Pre-War glamour meets state of the art technology to dazzle as each unit brings the grandeur of classic New York City into today's modern spotlight.

With grand proportions, home-like scale and fabulous layouts, 575 offers dream apartments to the sophisticated and the international alike. Co-op/condo quality fittings and finish are integral to each apartment. As a living alternative to the great expense and risk of apartment ownership in New York City, 575 provides a true home for the discerning resident. Many opt to start their family lives at 575, write the great American novel, or sell their current residence as a reserve living out their days in the splendor of a building built for the ages. There is much to dispute in our daily lives but certainly there can be no dispute with respect to the beauty and elegance of 575. Crossing the ages this last 110 years, this wonder of architecture has maintained its architectural and technological relevance at every step. They have the best technology and the latest software so that they can focus on what really matters: their clients. From the sale and rental of studios to the purchase of commercial spaces, our agents do it all.

One of New York Citys most highly regarded and sought-after neighborhoods, the Upper West Side is a picturesque example of big-city life in The Big Apple. With numerous entertainment venues and popular tourist attractions, Upper West Side is a lively residential area known for its extravagant apartments and luxurious condos that are home to some of New York Citys most affluent actors, artists, and public figures. Bounded by Central Park to the east and the Hudson River to the west, Upper West Side is a sprawling, centrally located Manhattan community that is easily accessible via the New York City Subway.
